sql:
SELECT session_rating, duration, resolution_time 
FROM chat_sessions 
WHERE user_id = 1 AND scenario_id = '0';

SELECT user_id, AVG(duration) AS average_duration
FROM chat_sessions
GROUP BY user_id;

SELECT chat_id, scenario_id, user_id, session_rating
FROM chat_sessions
WHERE scenario_id = '<SPECIFIED_SCENARIO_ID>' AND session_rating < 4;

SELECT cs.chat_id, a.agent_id
FROM chat_sessions cs
JOIN agents a ON INSTR(',' || cs.agent_ids || ',', ',' || a.agent_id || ',') > 0;

external_knowledge:
- "journey of each user" refers to the user's activity in different chat sessions;
- "journey across different scenarios" indicates the user's participation in various scenarios, each represented by a scenario-id;
- "average time spent in the clouds" is a metaphor for the average session duration;
- "stars they awarded for their experience" metaphorically represents the session ratings given by users;
- "average time to solve their cosmic queries" refers to the average resolution time for issues in the chat sessions;
- "the universe they ventured into" symbolizes the scenarios (scenario_id) each user was part of.
